HEADWORD: Crossbones
<hw>Cross"bones`</hw> <pr>(kr⟦ocr⟧s"b⟦omac⟧nz`)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<def>A representation of two of the leg bones or arm bones of a
skeleton, laid crosswise, often surmounted with a skull, and serving as
a symbol of death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Crossbones</qex>, scythes, hourglasses, and other lugubrious
emblems of mortality.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crossbow</ent>⟦br⟧
